This was the first ever YWA video I did, back in 2016. Surya Namaskar ‚â† Sun salutation. There is no sense of saluting a celestial object. In sanskrit the word Surya (‡§∏‡•Ç‡§∞‡•ç‡§Ø) has many meanings. Grammatical Surya means by whom or due to which other objects illuminates or get nourishment and energy. 
Surya namaskar is an exercise which effects your whole body that's why our ancestors called it Surya namaskar. Surya is one of the hundred names of God also because mediating and worshipping the formless God gives a lot of physical and spiritual power.
Our Aryan ancestors were the followers of Vedas in which idolatry and veneration of any object is prohibited. Namaste

It involves going into the mountain pose, followed by stretching one of your legs back and with the other leg going into a lunge like position with your knee at a ninety degree positioning and your hands stretched right above your head. Hey, a sun salutation is a rotation of right leg back and then left leg back. This sun salutation series is INCORRECT. After completing one half of the rotation with the right leg,  the series is repeated with the left leg STEPPING BACK.  This video leaves the body unbalanced as the series is not done correctly. Correctly it alternates right leg back, then left leg back. That then is ONE COMPLETE Sun Salutation.
